main event: A witness observed 3 bright green, dish-shaped objects traveling at speeds near 1000 mph in Garwood, New Jersey on February 30, 1972.
interesting points: The objects were visible for about 9-10 minutes instead of the reported 30 seconds.
One object was only visible for a matter of seconds, heading due north.
There were numerous conflicting points in the witness's report.
The witness felt the objects were likely aircraft.
The report includes photographs of the observed objects.
